Unions are calling for a boycott of the company’s products for embarking on a restructuring process and cutting jobs. The demonstrations are taking place across the country, including Cape Town and Johannesburg. General secretary Zwelinzima Vavi says government is a critical stakeholder and needs to help bring the strike to an end. “The strike has a devastating impact on the image of South Africa, here and abroad. Workers are making supreme sacrifices, we are convening a meeting on Tuesday, of all the people who are sympathetic to the cause, and who reject the presence of the Israeli company that is operating from the occupied territory of the Palestinian people.” #BoyCottClover march to Israel Trade and Economic offices in Sandton to demand an end to apartheid Israel pic.twitter.com/uZKDkhh5QJ — SAFTU (@SAFTU_media) January 27, 2022  Dairy company Clover and unions return to negotiation table: Zwelinzima Vavi  Clover Strike | Clover granted court order that unions must publicly denounce violence, intimidation: 